text: I have noticed that in the Fast3D samples that we clear for a longer time ( 2 weeks instead of overnight) although they are much more clear but there are some holes at the periphery of the sample. I can see the same effect on Fast3D samples that have been over a year. Is it normal that the aqueous clearing method can cause these holes? Anyone had a similar problem?
